UML:TaggedValue.value: Services can be completely removed from the system by authorized users.
Administrators can review the personal information of users so they can check it for completeness and reliability in order to give them new roles in the system.

The uStore will provide a mechanism for subscribing to ticket requests. A registered user (end user, developer, provider roles) will be able to subscribe to a selected set (category/keywords) of ticket requests.
During the project lifetime, task 3.4 partners will manage the server.

The uStore will provide a mechanism for viewing statistics about ticket request and their status. The statistics will include information about requester, category of service, response time, development time and developer/provider information
System can send notifications (via e-mail or other means), and they should contain hyperlinks for easy access to the mentioned services.
After the project lifetime, the consortium will manage the server

uStore will include ticketing system. Any registered user can open a ticket. There will be a mechanism for notifying the user about the his tickets status. The status will include information about:
  • How many times viewed
  • How many appearances in searches
  • If and when selected for implementation

The uStore will provide an interface for creating an advanced service request ticket.
The interface can be a web page or a tailored program.
The interface will allow refinement of existing tickets (simple and advanced). The interface should for specification of all the simple ticket elements, and in addition estimation of cost and required development effort.
A free text field for notes will be available.

Services should have a state of "not approved " / "invisible" and while in this state end users cannot see the service and cannot use it in any way. Administrators and the service owner still can see and edit the service and its metadata. After approving the service by administrator, the state will be changed.
